ry%20of%20geniuses%20in%20a%20datacenter.'%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-chaos-ai-arms-race-competitors-ethics-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleading%20AI%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20all%20competing%20to%20be%20the%20first%20to%20reach%20a%20single%20goal%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agi-artificial-general-intelligence-explained-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eartificial%20general%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAGI%20is%20generally%20considered%20to%20be%20a%20still%20theoretical%20version%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20that%20is%20capable%20of%20reasoning%20as%20well%20as%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20everyone%20agrees%20on%20how%20to%20define%20it.%20Dario%20Amodei%2C%20the%20cofounder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Anthropic%2C%20one%20of%20those%20leading%20AI%20companies%2C%20doesn't%20even%20agree%20on%20what%20to%20call%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmodei%20prefers%20to%20call%20it%20%26quot%3Bpowerful%20AI.%26quot%3B%20And%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdarioamodei.com%2Fmachines-of-loving-grace%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20essay%3C%2Fa%3E%20posted%20to%20Anthropic's%20website%2C%20Amodei%20defined%20the%20goal%3A%20a%20world%20driven%20by%20this%20emerging%20form%20of%20AI%2C%20one%20in%20which%20%26quot%3Beverything%20goes%20right.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%2C%20by%20comparison%2C%20says%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20develop%20%26quot%3BAI%20systems%20that%20are%20generally%20smarter%20than%20humans.%26quot%3B%20Google%20and%20Meta%20have%20also%20said%20they're%20working%20toward%20the%20same%20goal.%20However%2C%20no%20company%20has%20provided%20a%20more%20specific%20definition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20often%20turned%20off%20by%20the%20way%20many%20AI%20risk%20public%20figures%20(not%20to%20mention%20AI%20company%20leaders)%20talk%20about%20the%20post-AGI%20world%2C%20as%20if%20it's%20their%20mission%20to%20single-handedly%20bring%20it%20about%20like%20a%20prophet%20leading%20their%20people%20to%20salvation%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20dangerous%20to%20view%20companies%20as%20unilaterally%20shaping%20the%20world%2C%20and%20dangerous%20to%20view%20practical%20technological%20goals%20in%20essentially%20religious%20terms.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20wrote%20that%20he%20prefers%20to%20use%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bpowerful%20AI%26quot%3B%20because%20it's%20free%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bsci-fi%26quot%3B%20connotations%20of%20AGI.%20In%20his%20essay%2C%20he%20defined%20powerful%20AI%20as%20having%20the%20following%20properties%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20smart%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20smarter%20than%20a%20Nobel%20Prize%20winner%20across%20most%20relevant%20fields.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20multimodal%3A%20It%20isn't%20limited%20to%20one%20mode%20of%20action.%20It%20can%20interface%20through%20text%2C%20audio%2C%20video%2C%20mouse%20and%20keyboard%20control%2C%20and%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20independent%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20not%20just%20passively%20answer%20questions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20it%20can%20be%20given%20tasks%20that%20take%20hours%2C%20days%2C%20or%20weeks%20to%20complete%2C%20and%20then%20goes%20off%20and%20does%20those%20tasks%20autonomously.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20abstract%3A%20%26quot%3BIt%20does%20not%20have%20a%20physical%20embodiment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20replicable%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20resources%20used%20to%20train%20the%20model%20can%20be%20repurposed%20to%20run%20millions%20of%20instances%20of%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20fast.%20%26quot%3BThe%20model%20can%20absorb%20information%20and%20generate%20actions%20at%20roughly%2010x-100x%20human%20speed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%20cooperative.%20%26quot%3BEach%20of%20these%20million%20copies%20can%20act%20independently%2