3E%3Cp%3EDirector%20Bryan%20Bertino%20said%20he%20drew%20his%20main%20inspiration%20from%20an%20experience%20from%20his%20childhood%2C%20according%20to%20the%20film's%20production%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20kid%2C%20I%20lived%20in%20a%20house%20on%20a%20street%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20nowhere.%20One%20night%2C%20while%20our%20parents%20were%20out%2C%20somebody%20knocked%20on%20the%20front%20door%20and%20my%20little%20sister%20answered%20it.%20At%20the%20door%20were%20some%20people%20asking%20for%20somebody%20that%20didn't%20live%20there.%20We%20later%20found%20out%20that%20these%20people%20were%20knocking%20on%20doors%20in%20the%20area%20and%2C%20if%20no%20one%20was%20home%2C%20breaking%20into%20the%20houses%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Bertino.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFans%20of%20the%20film%20have%20also%20compared%20it%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcult-leader-charles-manson-dead-2017-11%5C%22%3EManson%20murders%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20unsolved%20murders%20of%20the%20Sharp%20family%2C%20known%20as%20the%20Keddie%20Cabin%20Murders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Exorcist%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20the%20most%20beloved%20horror%20films%20of%20all%20time%2C%20is%20about%20a%20preteen%20girl%20who%20becomes%20possessed%20by%20a%20demon.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22590%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20exorcist%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F4ea1a7e96bb3f7ee61000000%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22399%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Exorcist.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EWarner%20Bros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Exorcist%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20based%20on%20the%20story%20of%20a%2013-year-old%20boy%20known%20as%20Roland%20Doe%2C%20who%20began%20exhibiting%20strange%20behavior%20in%201949%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2017%2F02%2F04%2Fhow-a-suburban-boys-demonic-possession-inspired-the-exorcist%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Post.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0His%20family%20reported%20furniture%20moving%20on%20its%20own%2C%20scratches%20all%20over%20Doe's%20body%2C%20and%20loud%2C%20disembodied%20voices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20cross-country%20move%20and%20no%20change%20in%20Doe's%20strange%20behavior%2C%20his%20family%20enlisted%20the%20help%20of%20the%20Catholic%20church.%20One%20of%20the%20priests%20involved%20in%20the%20Doe%20case%2C%20Father%20Raymond%20Bishop%2C%20kept%20a%20diary%2C%20per%20The%20Daily%20Mail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20his%20entries%20stated%2C%20%26quot%3BAt%20midnight%2C%20the%20Fathers%20planned%20to%20give%20(Roland)%20Holy%20Communion%2C%20but%20Satan%20would%20have%20no%20part%20of%20it.%20Even%20while%20the%20institution%20of%20the%20Blessed%20Sacrament%20was%20explained%2C%20his%20body%20was%20badly%20scratched%20and%20branded.%20The%20word%20'HELLO'%20was%20printed%20on%20his%20chest%20and%20thigh.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20after%20multiple%20attempts%2C%20the%20%26quot%3Bdemon%26quot%3B%20was%20exorcised%2C%20and%20Doe%20returned%20to%20normal.%20He%20never%20spoke%20of%20the%20incident%20publicly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20real%20identity%20was%20revealed%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fskepticalinquirer.org%2F2021%2F10%2Fdemoniac-who-is-roland-doe-the-boy-who-inspired-the-exorcist%2F%5C%22%3EThe%20Skeptical%20Inquirer%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%3A%20Ronald%20E.%20Hunkeler.%20Hunkeler%20died%20in%202020%20at%20the%20age%20of%2086.%20Before%20that%2C%20he'd%20been%20an%20engineer%20at%20NASA%20and%2C%20according%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Post%2C%20was%20always%20afraid%20his%20colleagues%20would%20find%20out%20about%20his%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Exorcism%20of%20Emily%20Rose%26quot%3B%20is%20also%20about%20a%20girl%20possessed%20by%20a%20demon.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22485%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20exorcism%20of%20emily%20rose%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a78b9025c96b073038b456b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22321%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Exorcism%20of%20Emily%20Rose.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ESony%20Pictures%20Releasing%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20Anneliese%20Michel%2C%20a%20young%20German%20woman%20%E2%80%94%20renamed%20Emily%20Rose%20in%20the%20film%20%E2%80%94%20is%20tragic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Michel%20was%20a%20teenager%2C%20she%20experienced%20the%20first%20symptoms%20of%20her%20alleged%20possession.%20She%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20epilepsy%2C%20and%20given%20medication%20to%20help%20treat%20the%20disease%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Farchive%2Fpolitics%2F1978%2F04%2F21%2Fcries-of-a-woman-possessed%2F94bf2fd3-8e64-482d-869d-1f929851ca8f%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20meds%20didn't%20help.%20Michel%20continued%20to%20have%20seizures%2C%20and%20she%20began%20to%20claim%20she%20was%20having%20visions%20and%20hearing%20voices%20telling%20her%20she%20was%20a%20sinner.%20She%20became%20depressed%20and%20turned%20to%20religion%3A%20At%20her%20peak%2C%20she%20was%20genuflecting%20(kneeling)%20600%20times%20a%20day%2C%20eventually%20rupturing%20her%20knee%20ligaments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Michel%20was%2023%2C%20she%20had%20been%20treated%20with%20dozens%20of%20different%20medications%20(nothing%20helped)%2C%20and%20had%20undergone%2067%20exorcisms%20in%2010%20months%2C%20the%20Post%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20eventually%20stopped%20eating%20and%20died%20of%20starvation%20in%201976.%20She%20weighed%2068%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20parents%20and%20two%20of%20her%20priests%20were%20later%20found%20guilty%20of%20negligent%20homicide%20for%20allowing%20her%20to%20starve%2C%20per%20the%20German%20outlet%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fplanned-polish-exorcism-center-sparks-interest-in-germany%2Fa-3082751%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDW.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Texas%20Chain%20Saw%20Massacre%26quot%3B%20is%20about%20a%20group%20of%20hitchhikers%20who%20pick%20the%20wrong%20family%20to%20catch%20a%20ride%20from%20%E2%80%94%20they%20end%20up%20being%20cannibals.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22838%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22texas%20chainsaw%20massacre%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a78c249caba232d008b45d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22629%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELeatherface.%3Cp%3EBryanston%20Distributing%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20villain%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Texas%20Chain%20Saw%20Massacre%26quot%3B%20is%20Leatherface%2C%20who%20was%20based%20on%20real-life%20killer%20Ed%20Gein.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGein%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20La%20Crosse%2C%20Wisconsin%2C%20in%20the%20early%201900s%2C%20was%20obsessed%20with%20his%20mother%3B%20he%20rarely%20interacted%20with%20anyone%20besides%20her%2C%20and%20when%20she%20died%2C%20he%20spiraled%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.britannica.com%2Fbiography%2FEd-Gein%5C%22%3EEncyclopedia%C2%A0%20Britannica.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnown%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20Butcher%20of%20Plainfield%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20is%20suspected%20to%20have%20killed%20several%20victims%2C%20but%2C%20more%20disturbingly%2C%20he%20took%20to%20robbing%20the%20graves%20of%20recently%20buried%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20used%20their%20body%20parts%20to%20create%20something%20like%20a%20woman%20suit%20that%20he%20wore%2C%20pretending%20to%20be%20his%20mother%2C%20according%20to%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BDeviant.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20had%20lamps%2C%20belts%2C%20and%20bowls%20made%20out%20of%20human%20body%20parts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGein's%20story%20also%20partly%20inspired%20%26quot%3BPsycho%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Silence%20of%20the%20Lambs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BPoltergeist%26quot%3B%20tells%20the%20story%20of%20a%20family%20who%20buys%20a%20haunted%20house%20built%20on%20top%20of%20a%20Native%20American%20burial%20ground.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22844%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22poltergeist%20clown%20doll%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a78cee45c96b033008b460a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22633%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20terrifying%20clown%20doll%20from%20%26quot%3BPoltergeist.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EMGM%2FUA%20Entertainment%20Company%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plot%20of%201982%20classic%20%26quot%3BPoltergeist%26quot%3B%20was%20based%20on%20the%20Hermann%20family%20of%20Long%20Island%2C%20New%20York%2C%20who%20claimed%20to%20be%20haunted%20by%20a%20poltergeist%20that%20made%20objects%20fly%20through%20their%20home%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.ie%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DSlYEAAAAMBAJ%26lpg%3DPA55%26ots%3DiCect3kjyE%26dq%3Ddetective%2520tozzi%26pg%3DPA49%23v%3Donepage%26q%3Dporcelain%26f%3Dfalse%5C%22%3ELife%20Magazine.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Hermann%20family%20eventually%20moved%20away%2C%20but%20they%20maintained%20the%20house%20was%20haunted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20Stranger%20Calls%26quot%3B%20is%20about%20a%20babysitter%20who's%20being%20terrorized%20by%20a%20mysterious%20caller%20inside%20the%20house%20with%20her.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22when%20a%20stranger%20calls%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a78d57bcaba23a4028b45fd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECamila%20Belle%20in%20%26quot%3BWhen%20a%20Stranger%20Calls.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EScreen%20Gems%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20is%20based%20on%20the%20real%20unsolved%20murder%20of%2013-year-old%20Janett%20Christman%20in%201950.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.columbiatribune.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fgovernment%2F2010%2F03%2F07%2Fwho-killed-janett-christman%2F984978007%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EColumbia%20Daily%20Tribune%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote%2C%20Christman%20was%20babysitting%203-year-old%20Greg%20Romack%20when%20she%20called%20the%20Columbia%20Police%20Department%20and%20told%20them%20to%20%26quot%3Bcome%20quick%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20she%20hung%20up%20before%20the%20police%20could%20trace%20her%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Romacks%20returned%20home%2C%20they%20discovered%20Christman's%20body%20in%20a%20pool%20of%20blood.%20She%20had%20been%20raped%20and%20strangled%20with%20a%20cord.%20The%20police%20eventually%20ruled%20that%20it%20had%20been%20an%20%26quot%3Binside%20job%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20killer%20knew%20the%20house%20and%20its%20layout%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BDead%20Ringers%26quot%3B%20explores%20the%20mysterious%20deaths%20of%20a%20pair%20of%20co-dependent%20twin%20brothers.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22dead%20ringers%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a78d7c05c96b033008b4628%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJeremy%20Irons%20played%20both%20twins.%3Cp%3ETwentieth%20Century%20Fox%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Marcus%20twins%20shared%20a%20gynecology%20practice%2C%20an%20apartment%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20a%20house%20in%20the%20Hamptons%20%E2%80%94%20and%20eventually%20their%20deaths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApparently%2C%2045-year-old%20Stewart%20and%20Cyril%20Marcus%20were%20addicted%20to%20barbiturates%3B%20when%20their%20decomposing%20bodies%20were%20found%2C%20their%20mysterious%20deaths%20were%20first%20ruled%20as%20being%20caused%20by%20an%20overdose%2C%20then%20by%20withdrawal%20(they%20may%20have%20been%20attempting%20to%20wean%20themselves%20off%20the%20drugs)%2C%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20medical%20examiner%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20that%20Cyril%20outlived%20his%20brother%20by%20%3Cem%3Ea%20couple%20of%20days%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20continued%20to%20live%20in%20the%20apartment%20before%20eventually%20dying%20himself.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20received%20a%20TV%20reboot%20on%20Prime%20Video%20in%202023%2C%20starring%20Rachel%20Weisz.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BJaws%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20story%20of%20a%20small%20beachside%20town%20that's%20being%20terrorized%20by%20a%20vengeful%20shark.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22jaws%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F58c025090beac521008b460d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThey%20needed%20a%20bigger%20boat.%3Cp%3EJaws%2FIMDB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20terrifying%20tale%20of%20the%20most%20famous%20great%20white%20shark%20ever%20is%20based%20upon%20a%20string%20of%20shark%20attacks%20on%20the%20Jersey%20Shore%20in%201916.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fhistory%2Fthe-shark-attacks-that-were-the-inspiration-for-jaws-15220260%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESmithsonian%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2025-year-old%20Charles%20Vansant%20bled%20to%20death%20from%20a%20bite%20in%20Beach%20Haven%2C%20New%20Jersey.%20Five%20days%20later%20%E2%80%94%20and%2045%20miles%20north%20%E2%80%94%20a%20bellhop%20from%20Spring%20Lake%20also%20bled%20to%20death%20from%20a%20shark%20bite.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20only%20gets%20more%20terrifying.%20The%20same%20shark%20then%20swam%2030%20miles%20north%20and%2010%20miles%20%3Cem%3Einland%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20killing%20both%20a%20boy%20and%20a%20man%20trying%20to%20save%20the%20boy%20in%20a%20creek%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nj.com%2Finside-jersey%2F2016%2F07%2Fdeadly_shark_attacks_terrorized_new_jersey_in_1916_could_it_happen_again.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENJ.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20fifth%20victim%20was%20attacked%2030%20minutes%20later%20in%20the%20same%20creek%20%E2%80%94%20he%20survived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NJ.com%2C%20George%20Burgess%2C%20an%20ichthyologist%20(a%20scientist%20who%20concentrates%20on%20the%20study%20of%20fish)%2C%20called%20it%20the%20%26quot%3Bmost%20unique%20set%20of%20shark%20attacks%20that%20have%20ever%20occurred.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Girl%20Next%20Door%26quot%3B%20is%20about%20a%20boy%20who%20tries%20to%20save%20his%20neighbor%20from%20her%20twisted%20adopted%20family.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20girl%20next%20door%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a78de2bcaba231f008b4661%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Girl%20Next%20Door.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EModern%20Distributors%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20murder%20of%20Sylvia%20Likens%20is%20known%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bworst%20crime%20in%20Indiana%20history%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indystar.com%2Fstory%2Flife%2F2015%2F10%2F25%2Fwhen-sylvia-likens-killed-part-our-childhoods-died-too%2F74212178%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndy%20Star%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20Likens%20was%20just%2016%20when%20she%20was%20found%20dead%20in%20the%20basement%20of%20her%20temporary%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20carnival-worker%20parents%20left%20Sylvia%20and%20her%20sister%20in%20the%20care%20of%20Gertrude%20Baniszewski%2C%20a%20mother%20of%20seven%2C%20paying%20Baniszewski%20by%20the%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20later%2C%20on%20October%2026%2C%201965%2C%20police%20found%20Sylvia's%20emaciated%20corpse%2C%20apparently%20covered%20in%20hundreds%20of%20wounds%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indianapolismonthly.com%2Flongform%2Flikens-looking-back-indianas-infamous-crime-50-years-later%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIndianapolis%20Monthly%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote.%20Baniszewski%20%E2%80%94%20with%20the%20help%20of%20some%20of%20her%20children%20and%20a%20few%20neighborhood%20kids%20%E2%80%94%20had%20tortured%20the%20girl%20to%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBaniszewski%20was%20sentenced%20to%2021%20years%20in%20prison%2C%20but%20she%20was%20eventually%20released%20on%20parole.%20The%20rest%20of%20the%20children%20who%20were%20involved%20served%20between%20two%20and%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Possession%26quot%3B%20is%20the%20tale%20of%20a%20family%20being%20tortured%20by%20a%20demon%20inside%20a%20dybbuk%20box.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20possession%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a7cca22433c01be008b45f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBefore%20killing%20zombies%20on%20%26quot%3BThe%20Walking%20Dead%2C%26quot%3B%20Jeffrey%20Dean%20Morgan%20starred%20in%20this%20horror%20flick.%3Cp%3ELionsgate%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Haxton%20posted%20the%20real%20dybbuk%20box%20on%20eBay%20with%20a%20chilling%20description%20of%20events%20that%20befell%20him%20after%20he%20bought%20it%20at%20an%20estate%20sale%2C%20wrote%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mysanantonio.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Farticle%2Fstory-of-haunted-box-isn-t-just-a-tale-dreamed-up-3882396.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMy%20San%20Antonio%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20claimed%20that%20he%20bought%20the%20box%20for%20his%20mom's%20birthday%20and%20that%20she%20almost%20instantaneously%20had%20a%20stroke%20upon%20receiving%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.riverfronttimes.com%2Fnews%2Fdevils-wine-box-missouris-tie-to-the-possession-2500991%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERiverfront%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20claimed%20that%20the%20final%20straw%20that%20inspired%20him%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20box%20was%20when%20his%20sister%2C%20brother%2C%20and%20brother's%20wife%20all%20stayed%20over%2C%20and%20each%20one%20reported%20having%20the%20same%20exact%20nightmare%2C%20according%20to%20a%20reposting%20of%20the%20original%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdibbukbox.com%2Fstory.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EeBay%20listing%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20might%20be%20wondering%C2%A0what%20exactly%20a%20dybbuk%20is.%20According%20to%20Encyclopedia%20Britannica%2C%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bdisembodied%20human%20spirit%20that%2C%20because%20of%20former%20sins%2C%20wanders%20restlessly%20until%20it%20finds%20a%20haven%20in%20the%20body%20of%20a%20living%20person%26quot%3B%20that%20originated%20in%20Jewish%20folklore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Rite%26quot%3B%20is%20based%20upon%20the%20life%20of%20a%20real%20priest%2C%20Father%20Gary%20Thomas%2C%20and%20his%20time%20at%20the%20Vatican%20while%20training%20to%20become%20an%20exorcist.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221334%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22the%20rite%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a78dea05c96b01d008b4634%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnthony%20Hopkins%20in%20%26quot%3BThe%20Rite.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EWarner%20Bros.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Rite%26quot%3B%20is%20based%20on%20the%20life%20of%20Father%20Gary%20Thomas%2C%20a%20priest%20who%20is%20one%20of%2014%20Vatican-certified%20exorcists%20who%20works%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5