%20wave%20of%20distress%20in%20coming%20years.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERun-down%2C%20vacant%20offices%20could%20be%20sold%20in%20fire%20sales%20as%20owners%20cut%20their%20losses.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThat%20might%20be%20good%20news%20for%20housing%20supply%20as%20former%20offices%20get%20converted%20to%20apartments%2C%20industry%20vets%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate-big-trouble-crash-bank-crisis-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseismic%20event%20is%20brewing%20in%20a%20corner%20of%20the%20commercial%20real%20estate%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20many%20office%20buildings%20facing%20distress%20as%20they%20approach%20a%20wall%20of%20maturing%20debt%20and%20struggle%20against%20enduring%20work-from-home%20trends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20factors%20%E2%80%94%20which%20have%20left%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20office%20buildings%20nearly%20deserted%20%E2%80%94%20are%20about%20to%20spark%20a%20handful%20of%20fire%20sales%2C%20potentially%20kicking%20off%20a%20wave%20of%20office-to-apartment%20conversions%20that%20will%20add%20more%20housing%20supply%20to%20the%20pipeline%2C%20real%20estate%20pros%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERichard%20Barkham%2C%20the%20chief%20global%20economist%20of%20commercial%20real%20estate%20investment%20firm%20CBRE%2C%20says%20he%20sees%20an%20upheaval%20of%20Class%20B%20office%20buildings%20%E2%80%94%20a%20segment%20of%20office%20properties%20that%20struggle%20to%20attract%20tenants%2C%20mainly%20due%20to%20being%20older%20and%20in%20need%20of%20renovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20second-tier%20properties%20have%20vacancy%20rates%20as%20high%20as%2080%25%2C%20he%20said%2C%20predicting%20that%20many%20could%20be%20ripped%20down%20or%20transformed%20over%20the%20next%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20banks%20are%20going%20to%20have%20to%20dispose%20of%20that%20real%20estate%2C%26quot%3B%20Barkham%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview.%20%26quot%3BSo%20we%20will%20see.%20I%20think%20over%20the%20next%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20will%20pay%20out%20over%20two%20to%20three%20years%20%E2%80%94%20I%20think%20we'll%20see%20a%20wave%20of%20offices%20going%20back%20to%20banks%2C%20and%20I%20say%2C%20they'll%20be%20firesold%20and%20either%20demolished%20or%20converted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20chain%20reaction%20already%20looks%20to%20be%20in%20the%20works%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fcommercial-real-estate-debt-crisis-credit-crunch-bank-loans-default-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebanks%20quietly%20shedding%3C%2Fa%3E%20troubled%20office%20properties%20from%20their%20balance%20sheets%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nyc-office-buildings-towers-became-housing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econversions%3C%2Fa%3E%20starting%20to%20trickle%20into%20the%20mix.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCREACBW027SBOG%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etotal%20amount%20of%20commercial%20real%20estate%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%20by%20commercial%20banks%20declined%20to%20%242.9%20trillion%2C%20down%20from%20a%20peak%20of%20%243%20trillion%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELarge%20banks%20have%20been%20pulling%20back%20on%20lending%20to%20the%20sector%2C%20with%2074%25%20saying%20they%20tightened%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCOMREPUSQ159N%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estandards%20for%20nonresidential%20commercial%20real%20estate%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%20of%202024%2C%20Federal%20Reserve%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rentcafe.com%2Fblog%2Frental-market%2Fadaptive-reuse-office-to-apartments-2024%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFrom%2520Boardrooms%2520to%2520Bedrooms%253A%2520A%2CConversions%2520Expected%2520in%2520Major%2520Cities%26amp%3Btext%3DFrom%25202021%2520to%25202024%252C%2520the%2Cincreased%2520from%252012%252C100%2520to%252055%252C300.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoffice%20spaces%20scheduled%20to%20be%20converted%20into%20apartments%3C%2Fa%3E%20rose%20to%2055%2C000%20in%202024%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20office-to-apartment%20conversions%20recorded%20in%20four%20years%2C%20and%20a%20357%25%20increase%20from%20levels%20recorded%20in%202021%2C%20according%20to%20Yardi%20Matrix%20data%20cited%20by%20RentCafe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Vavas%2C%20a%20real%20estate%20finance%20attorney%20at%20Polsinelli%20who%20works%20with%20commercial%20real%20estate%20lenders%2C%20has%20worked%20on%20a%20handful%20of%20office-to-residential%20conversion%20deals%20this%20year.%20He%20had%20never%20worked%20on%20that%20kind%20of%20deal%20prior%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20he%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.deloitte.com%2Fus%2Fen%2Finsights%2Feconomy%2Fspotlight%2Foffice-sector-in-commercial-real-estate-lending.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOffices%20account%20for%20around%2020%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20square%20footage%20of%20all%20CRE%20properties%2C%20and%20the%20worst-performing%20buildings%20account%20for%20around%2010%25%20of%20the%20total%20office%20supply%2C%20Barkham%20estimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yardimatrix.com%2FPublications%2FDownload%2FFile%2F6080-MatrixOfficeNationalReport-August2024%3Feml%3Djsor%2540businessinsider.com%26frm%3D4%26key%3D86DF904366A655EFD483DCB636266BC4922525FA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E1.2%20billion%20square%20feet%20worth%20of%20office%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20could%20be%20spun%20into%20residential%20space%2C%20Yardi%20said%20in%20a%20separate%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20CBRE%20analysis%20of%20planned%2C%20ongoing%2C%20and%20completed%20office-to-residential%20conversions%20since%202016%20estimates%20that%201.38%20billion%20square%20feet%20worth%20of%20office%20space%20could%20be%20converted.%20Barkham%20said%20the%20evolution%20could%20take%20around%20a%20decade%20to%20fully%20take%20place%20in%20cities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20these%20kinds%20of%20conversions%20are%20costly%20and%20difficult.%20In%20New%20York%2C%20architects%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-nyc-office-buildings-towers-became-housing-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20holes%20in%20skyscrapers%20to%20rearrange%20square%20footage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20Silverstein%20Properties%2C%20one%20of%20New%20York's%20largest%20commercial%20landlords%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fa-new-york-developer-is-spending-15-billion-to-turn-offices-to-apartments-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eis%20spending%20%241.5%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20convert%20some%20of%20its%20office%20buildings.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20for%20landlords%20facing%20a%20glut%20of%20unwanted%20space%2C%20it%20could%20be%20worth%20it%20to%20try%20to%20covert%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20solid%20base%20of%20really%20badly%20performing%20offices%20that's%20going%20to%20go%20bust%20over%20the%20course%20of%202025%2C%26quot%3B%20Barkham%20added.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20quite%20clear%20that%20we%20don't%20need%20as%20much%20office%20space%20in%20the%20United%20States%20as%20we%20did.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225bc9d833-39a3-40c9-a071-6c0d943a3acd%5C%22%3EThe%20office%20market's%20new%20era%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20high-quality%20buildings%20are%20being%20filled%2C%20demand%20for%20offices%20has%20generally%20sagged%20since%20the%20pandemic%2C%20when%20remote%20work%20became%20much%20more%20widespread.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.commercialedge.com%2Fblog%2Fnational-office-report%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520national%2520average%2520full%252Dservice%2CDiego%2527s%2520by%2520310%2520basis%2520points.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20office%20vacancy%20rate%20was%2019.4%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%2C%20according%20to%20the%20data%20provider%20CommercialEdge%2C%20up%20200%20basis%20points%20from%20the%20prior%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FDRCRELEXFACBS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELate%20payments%20on%20commercial%20real%20estate%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20climbed%20to%201.42%25%20in%20the%20second%20quarter%2C%20the%20highest%20rate%20in%20nearly%2010%20years.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FCOMREPUSQ159N%230%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECommercial%20real%20estate%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20dropped%20another%209%25%20year-over-year%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20Fed%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20real%20estate%20investors%20have%20warmed%20up%20to%20the%20sector%20over%20the%20past%20six%20months%2C%20Vavas%20says%2C%20thanks%20partly%20to%20buildings%20being%20sold%20at%20steep%20discounts%20and%20banks%20attempting%20to%20dump%20loans%20from%20their%20balance%20sheets.%20He%20recalls%20a%20deal%20he%20worked%20on%20recently%2C%20where%20the%20property%20owner%20priced%20the%20building%20at%20a%2020%25-30%25%20discount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20people%20who%20owned%20it%2C%20the%20building%20was%20heavily%20vacant%20and%20they%20just%20wanted%20to%2C%20I%20think%2C%20cut%20their%20losses%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20defunct%20offices%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20converted%20into%20residential%20properties%20given%20the%20shortage%20of%20housing%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Vavas%20says.%20The%20office-to-residential%20conversion%20is%20the%20most%20common%20type%20of%20conversion%20project%2C%20according%20to%20Yardi%20data%2C%20accounting%20for%2038%25%20of%20all%20conversions%20in%20the%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20idea%20of%20people%20being%20in%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%20versus%20five%20days%20a%20week%20was%20the%20exception%2C%20not%20the%20standard.%20And%20now%20it's%20the%20opposite%2C%26quot%3B%20Vavas%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20do%20that%20across%20a%20company%2C%20by%20definition%2C%20your%20demand%20is%20going%20to%20drop.%20And%20when%20it%20drops%20as%20a%20result%20of%20this%20post-pandemic%20thought%20of%20being%20back%20in%20the%20office%2C%20then%20I%20think%20you%20have%20to%20start%20to%20look%20at%2C%20well%2C%20I%20have%20this%20space.%20What%20are%20the%20needs%20for%20the%20community%2C%20for%20the%20location%3F%20And%20in%20New%20York%2C%20it%20just%20happens%20to%20be%20residential.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWashington%20DC%2C%20New%20York%20City%2C%20Dallas%2C%20Chicago%2C%20and%20Los%20Angeles%20have%20recorded%20the%20most%20office-to-apartment%20conversion%20starts%20this%20year%2C%20with%20a%20combined%2019%2C462%20conversions%20in%20the%20pipeline%2C%20Yardi%20data%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommutes%20will%20likely%20be%20shorter%20on%20average%2C%20and%20cities%20with%20many%20vacant%20offices%20could%20see%20more%20stores%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20theaters%20creep%20into%20the%20mix%2C%20Barkham%20says.%20He%20notes%2C%20though%2C%20that%20changes%20won't%20happen%20overnight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20will%20see%20vacant%20buildings%2C%20and%20you%20will%20see%20see-through%20offices%20for%20some%20considerable%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Barkham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate-office-outlook-fire-sales-apartment-conversions-housing-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728736262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67053e6f198738e3a70f00ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommercial-real-estate-office-outlook-fire-sales-apartment-conversions-housing-2024-10%22%2