ate%20sector%20businesses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Chinese%20stocks%20plunged%20ahead%20of%20Saturday's%20meeting%20as%20questions%20grew%20over%20the%20government's%20plans.%20The%20benchmark%20CSI%20300%20fell%207.1%25%20on%20Wednesday%20%E2%80%94%20its%20biggest%20one-day%20fall%20since%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lack%20of%20specific%20details%20on%20the%20size%20of%20the%20new%20stimulus%20package%20will%20hence%20leave%20investors%20wanting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20strength%20of%20the%20announced%20fiscal%20stimulus%20plan%20is%20weaker%20than%20expected.%20There's%20no%20timetable%2C%20no%20amount%2C%20no%20details%20of%20how%20the%20money%20will%20be%20spent%2C%26quot%3B%20Huang%20Yan%2C%20an%20investment%20manager%20at%20Shanghai%20QiuYang%20Capital%20Co%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fchina%2Fchinas-stimulus-message-leaves-investors-wanting-though-hanging-onto-hope-2024-10-12%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-to-increase-debt-issuance-in-bid-to-revive-economy-2024-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728734832000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670a550d3f2165d716e0788b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-to-increase-debt-issuance-in-bid-to-revive-economy-2024-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22China%20slipped%20into%20deflation%20in%202023%20as%20a%20result%20of%20weak%20domestic%20demand%20and%20a%20struggling%20property%20market.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rrommen%40insider.com%20(Rebecca%20Rommen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A22%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-to-increase-debt-issuance-in-bid-to-revive-economy-2024-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Where%20you%20should%20look%20for%20a%20job%20if%20you%20can't%20break%20into%20consulting%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Harvard%20career%20advisor%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224252%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Student%20walking%20on%20campus%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6709bdb66ac7b701e7cab1d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222834%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Harvard%20career%20adviser%20says%20students%20should%20consider%20options%20other%20than%20consulting.%3Cp%3EMaddie%20Meyer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJobs%20at%20consulting%20firms%20have%20long%20been%20prized%20by%20new%20grads%20and%20MBAs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Harvard%20career%20advisor%20says%20there%20are%20other%20ways%20to%20jump-start%20your%20career%20beyond%20consulting.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20recommends%20looking%20for%20companies%20that%20have%20dedicated%20early-career%20rotational%20programs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20landing%20a%20job%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-firms-mckinsey-bcg-accenture-workers-leaving-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etop%20consulting%20firm%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20the%20ultimate%20dream%20for%20many%20business%20students%2C%20not%20everyone%20who%20applies%20will%20make%20the%20cut%20%E2%80%94%20and%20some%20young%20professionals%20may%20be%20less%20interested%20in%20the%20industry%20than%20the%20MBAs%20that%20came%20before%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20new%20grads%20who%20still%20want%20the%20breadth%20of%20experience%20that%20generally%20comes%20with%20working%20in%20consulting%2C%20there%20are%20other%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGorick%20Ng%2C%20a%20Harvard%20University%20career%20advisor%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gorick.com%2Funspokenrules%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Unspoken%20Rules%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20many%20students%20are%20laser-focused%20on%20landing%20a%20consulting%20job%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthere%20are%20also%20many%20more%20students%20who%20just%20want%20to%20get%20a%20solid%20foothold%20in%20the%20early%20steps%20in%20their%20career.%20And%20consulting%20firms%20provide%20a%20great%20toehold%20for%20doing%20so%2C%20but%20they're%20not%20the%20only%20ones%20that%20offer%20a%20great%20toehold%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsulting%20has%20long%20been%20alluring%20to%20young%20professionals%20who%20are%20drawn%20in%20by%20the%20prestige%20that%20comes%20with%20working%C2%A0at%20one%20of%20the%20major%20firms.%20Ng%20said%20those%20firms%20tend%20to%20do%20a%20great%20job%20at%20creating%20a%20sense%20of%20FOMO%20%E2%80%94%20or%20fear%20of%20missing%20out%20%E2%80%94%20on%20campus%2C%20with%20many%20students%20feeling%20pressured%20to%20pursue%20those%20jobs%20largely%20because%20the%20people%20around%20them%20frame%20them%20as%20the%20ultimate%20catch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Ng%20said%20he's%20seen%20an%20uptick%20in%20students%20who%20land%20an%20internship%20with%20a%20consulting%20firm%20and%20afterward%20choose%20not%20to%20return%20for%20a%20full-time%20role.%20Part%20of%20that%20he%20attributes%20to%20the%20way%20Gen%20Z%20grads%20in%20particular%20are%20increasingly%20seeking%20meaning%20in%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20getting%20sucked%20into%20the%20allure%20of%20consulting%20by%20default%2C%20he%20encourages%20students%20to%20look%20for%20other%20ways%20to%20get%20some%20of%20the%20benefits%20that%20come%20with%20starting%20a%20career%20in%20consulting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20dedicated%20early-career%20programs%20come%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsulting-has-a-gen-z-problem-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EYoung%20consultants%3C%2Fa%3E%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20perks%20to%20their%20jobs%20was%20that%20they%20were%20able%20to%20learn%20a%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20and%20very%20quickly.%20Working%20on%20different%20projects%20every%20few%20months%20allowed%20them%20to%20gain%20a%20lot%20of%20work%20experience%20and%20get%20a%20better%20idea%20of%20what%20kinds%20of%20roles%20they%20will%20ultimately%20want%20to%20pursue%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20said%20those%20are%20the%20exact%20kinds%20of%20perks%20that%20new%20grads%20can%20get%20at%20companies%20with%20early-career%20programs.%20Some%20of%20the%20best%20programs%20to%20look%20for%20are%20those%20that%20offer%20one-%20or%20two-year%20rotational%20programs%20that%20allow%20the%20new%20hire%20to%20rotate%20between%20different%20aspects%20of%20the%20business%2C%20such%20as%20sales%2C%20marketing%2C%20HR%2C%20or%20operations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConsulting%20is%20an%20opportunity%20to%20see%20a%20wide%20variety%20of%20people%2C%20of%20types%20of%20business%20problems%2C%20of%20different%20contexts%2C%26quot%3B%20Ng%20said.%20%26quot%3BMore%20and%20more%20corporates%20are%20coming%20to%20realize%20that%20actually%20they%20can%20offer%20quite%20a%20competitive%20experience%20through%20these%20leadership%20development%20and%20rotational%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20said%20that%20one%20of%20the%20most%20impressive%20students%20he%20has%20mentored%20was%20gunning%20for%20a%20role%20at%20a%20consulting%20firm%20but%20that%20the%20competition%20was%20fierce.%20He%20looked%20for%20other%20options%20and%20ended%20up%20accepting%20a%20role%20at%20a%20media%20company%20in%20its%20leadership%20development%20program%20for%20early%20professionals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20has%20compiled%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gorick.com%2Fearly-career-employers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elist%20of%20more%20than%201%2C000%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20have%20early-career%20programs.%20He%20recommended%20young%20professionals%20filter%20the%20list%20by%20industries%20they%20are%20interested%20in.%20For%20those%20who%20are%20unsure%20what%20industries%20those%20would%20be%2C%20he%20said%20to%20simply%20consider%20which%20words%20sound%20the%20most%20intriguing%20or%20which%20brands%20are%20ones%20they%20actually%20engage%20with%20in%20their%20daily%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Ng's%20favorite%20companies%20to%20direct%20young%20professionals%20to%20are%20GE%2C%20Fifth%20Third%20Bank%2C%20Aon%2C%20CNBC%2FNBC%20Universal%2C%20Grainger%2C%20and%20Salesforce.%20He's%20worked%20with%20people%20at%20each%20of%20these%20companies%20whose%20job%20it%20is%20to%20ensure%20early-career%20talent%20can%20learn%20a%20lot%20and%20have%20access%20to%20resources%20needed%20to%20advance%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20tech%20companies%20with%20dedicated%20early-career%20programs%2C%20his%20list%20includes%20companies%20such%20as%20Nvidia%2C%20PayPal%2C%20Snap%2C%20Dropbox%2C%20Zoom%2C%20and%20Workday.%20And%20if%20you're%20interested%20in%20finance%2C%20some%20of%20the%20top%20companies%20with%20programs%20for%20new%20grads%20are%20UBS%2C%20Deutsche%20Bank%2C%20Goldman%20Sachs%2C%20and%20Piper%20Sandler%2C%20per%20his%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20said%20that%20although%20consulting%20can%20be%20a%20great%20career%20and%20an%20entry-level%20job%2C%20it%20should%20not%20necessarily%20be%20the%20default%20goal%20of%20every%20ambitious%20student%2C%20adding%20he%20thinks%20%26quot%3Bmost%20people%20want%20to%20become%20consultants%20because%20they%20were%20told%20by%20their%20friends%20that%20it's%20'prestigious.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20there's%20such%20a%20bigger%20world%20out%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20you%20may%20find%20%E2%80%94%20as%20many%20people%20do%20too%20late%20%E2%80%94%20that%20there's%20actually%20a%20more%20direct%20path%20to%20doing%20what%20you%20want%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%