iyatama-sharma-child-sexual-abuse-survivor-education-women-educate-your-girls%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%228%20Indian%20Heroes%20Who%20Became%20Legends%20in%20Wildlife%20Conservation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20story%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%20in%20India%20is%20not%20just%20about%20battling%20an%20overbearing%2C%20cruel%20and%20amoral%20system%20of%20governance%20but%20also%20about%20overcoming%20ignorance%20and%20public%20apathy.%20That%20is%20why%20on%20World%20Animal%20Welfare%20Day%2C%20it%20feels%20pertinent%20to%20highlight%20the%20contributions%20of%20certain%20individuals%20in%20our%20past%20who%20not%20only%20challenged%20the%20status%20quo%20but%20also%20raised%20public%20consciousness%20and%20inspired%20action%20against%20the%20incredible%20cruelty%20met%20to%20our%20precious%20wildlife.%20To%20keep%20alive%20the%20memory%20of%20their%20work%20is%20to%20remember%20what%20it%20means%20to%20preserve%20our%20wildlife.%20%3Cem%3E(Above%20images%20of%20Kailash%20Sankhala%2C%20J%20Vijaya%20%26amp%3B%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E1.%20Rinchen%20Wangchuk%3A%20What%20it%20means%20to%20co-exist%20with%20snow%20leopards%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20a%20famous%20father%20in%20Colonel%20Chewang%20Rinchen%2C%20a%20decorated%20Ladakhi%20soldier%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F246169%2Fladakh-snow-leopard-conservancy-india-trust-saviours-rinchen-wangchuk-tsewang-namgail-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERinchen%20Wangchuk%3C%2Fa%3E%20forged%20his%20own%20path.%20As%20a%20wildlife%20researcher%20from%20Ladakh%2C%20he%20framed%20a%20question%20that%20would%20address%20the%20fundamental%20challenge%20of%20snow%20leopard%20conservation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20you%20reconcile%20the%20notion%20of%20snow%20leopard%20conservation%20with%20the%20needs%20of%20local%20communities%20who%20lose%20their%20livestock%2C%20particularly%20sheep%20and%20goats%2C%20to%20these%20elusive%20creatures%3F%20To%20answer%20this%20question%2C%20he%20established%20the%20Snow%20Leopard%20Conservancy-India%20Trust%20(SLC-IT)%20in%202000%20to%20promote%20local%20efforts%20towards%20community-based%20conservation%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20taking%20a%20variety%20of%20steps%20to%20help%20local%20farmers%20and%20nomads%20protect%20their%20livestock%20from%20snow%20leopards%2C%20thus%20preventing%20man-animal%20conflicts%2C%20he%20also%20pioneered%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20models%20of%20eco-tourism%20with%20conservation-linked%20homestays%20located%20in%20critical%20snow%20leopard%20habitats%20and%20along%20popular%20trekking%20routes.%20These%20successful%20models%20of%20community-based%20tourism%20in%20the%20Hemis%20National%20Park%2C%20the%20Sham%20region%2C%20and%20Zanskar%20still%20stand%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20tragically%20passed%20away%20at%20the%20age%20of%20just%2042%20in%202011%20due%20to%20a%20deteriorating%20neurological%20condition%20but%20not%20before%20leaving%20behind%20a%20stellar%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E2.%20Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%3A%20The%20forest%20officer%20who%20showed%20India%20how%20to%20protect%20tigers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnown%20for%20his%20trademark%20long%20handlebar%20moustache%2C%20olive-coloured%20safari%20hat%20and%20dashing%20dark%20glasses%2C%20the%20late%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F234711%2Fhow-does-india-protect-tigers-fateh-singh-rathore-ranthambhore-national-park-rajasthan-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20the%20principal%20architect%20behind%20the%20success%20story%20that%20is%20the%20Ranthambhore%20National%20Park.%20As%20a%20ranger%2C%20warden%2C%20and%20field%20director%20at%20one%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20best-known%20tiger%20preserves%2C%20Fateh%E2%80%99s%20work%20emphasised%20three%20things%20%E2%80%94%20natural%20regeneration%20of%20the%20habitat%2C%20constant%20engagement%20with%20local%20communities%20living%20in%20its%20vicinity%20that%20went%20way%20beyond%20consultations%2C%20and%20an%20abiding%20love%20for%20the%20creatures%20who%20inhabited%20this%20forest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20became%20the%20blueprint%20for%20what%20a%20successful%20tiger%20conservation%20strategy%20looks%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F08%2F05103523%2FFateh_Singh_Rathore_2008-500x693.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fateh%20Singh%20Rathore%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-234723%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22693%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EFateh%20Singh%20Rathore%20(Image%20courtesy%20Wikimedia%20Commons)%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFateh%E2%80%99s%20approach%20to%20conservation%20was%20marked%20by%20his%20incredible%20knowledge%20of%20the%20terrain%20inside%20Ranthambore%E2%80%99s%20core%20area%20and%20the%20depth%20of%20his%20engagement%20with%20the%20local%20community%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it%20was%20relocating%2016%20villages%20inhabited%20in%20the%20core%20area%20of%20the%20National%20Park%20and%20ensuring%20that%20the%20village%20economy%20thrived%20despite%20this%20resettlement%20and%20a%20crackdown%20on%20poaching.%20He%20nearly%20died%20for%20his%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20as%20a%20forest%20officer%2C%20his%20loyalties%20only%20lay%20with%20the%20forests%20and%20not%20politicians%20or%20superior%20officers%20%E2%80%94%20a%20feature%20of%20his%20work%20that%20would%20come%20at%20a%20great%20personal%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E3.%20Jamal%20Ara%3A%20The%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20era%20when%20the%20field%20of%20ornithology%20was%20dominated%20by%20men%2C%20Jamal%20Ara%20stood%20out%20as%20a%20pioneer.%20It%20was%20the%20legendary%20ornithologist%20Salim%20Ali%20who%20called%20her%20the%20first%20%E2%80%98Birdwoman%E2%80%99%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20present-day%20Jharkhand%2C%20her%20work%20on%20the%20ornithology%20of%20the%20Chota%20Nagpur%20plateau%20%E2%80%9Cremains%20the%20only%20comprehensive%20study%20of%20birds%20in%20the%20region%20till%20date%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20an%20essay%20by%20wildlife%20historian%20Raza%20Kazmi%20titled%20%3Cem%3EThe%20First%20Lady%20of%20Indian%20Ornithology%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%94%20published%20in%20a%20recent%20collection%20of%20essays%20titled%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.in%2FWOMEN-WILD-Brilliant-Wildlife-Biologists%2Fdp%2F9353451817%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EWomen%20in%20the%20Wild%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3Eedited%20by%20Anita%20Mani.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20only%20studying%20till%20Class%2010%2C%20she%20was%20a%20prolific%20writer%20on%20the%20subject%20of%20birds.%20According%20to%20Kazmi%2C%20from%201949%20to%201988%2C%20she%20contributed%20to%20more%20than%2060%20papers%20and%20published%20articles%20to%20journals%20including%20the%20Bombay%20Natural%20History%20Society%20and%20Bengal%20Natural%20History%20Society%2C%20and%20the%20Newsletter%20for%20Birdwatchers%2C%20a%20publication%20read%20by%20amateur%20and%20professional%20ornithologists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20she%20also%20wrote%20a%20small%20booklet%20for%20children%20titled%20%3Cem%3EWatching%20Birds%20%3C%2Fem%3Epublished%20by%20the%20National%20Book%20Trust%20(NBT).%20The%20book%20is%20currently%20in%20its%2013th%20edition%20and%20it%20continues%20to%20educate%20children%20on%20the%20birds%20of%20India%20in%20multiple%20languages%20till%20this%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeyond%20her%20prolific%20writing%2C%20she%20also%20raised%20awareness%20among%20the%20masses%20through%20her%20programmes%20in%20All%20India%20Radio%20(AIR)%20and%20also%20dabbled%20in%20journalism%20for%20mainstream%20publication.%20%E2%80%9CMore%20importantly%2C%20in%20those%20days%2C%20she%20was%20the%20only%20spokesperson%20for%20Bihar%E2%80%99s%20imperilled%20wilderness%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20went%20beyond%20just%20advocating%20for%20birds%2C%20according%20to%20Raza.%20Her%20prescriptions%20and%20recommendations%20would%20lay%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20groundwork%20for%20modern%20conservation%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E4.%20Kailash%20Sankhala%3A%20The%20unsung%20hero%20who%20changed%20the%20destiny%20of%20tigers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F223419%2Fpadma-shri-kailash-sankhala-project-tiger-kanha-sariska-india-unsung-hero-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKailash%20Sankhala%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20first%20director%20of%20Project%20Tiger%2C%20played%20a%20fundamental%20role%20in%20turning%20the%20tide%20for%20wildlife%20conservation%20in%20India%2C%20particularly%20of%20tigers.%20A%20pioneering%20field%20officer%2C%20he%20did%20real%20field%20research%20work%20to%20understand%20the%20secretive%20lives%20of%20tigers%20from%20their%20behaviour%2C%20population%20dynamics%20to%20daily%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20all%20this%20work%20was%20triggered%20by%20an%20incident%20in%20the%20early%201950s%20when%20he%20killed%20a%20tiger.%20Riddled%20by%20guilt%2C%20it%20transformed%20him%20from%20a%20forest%20officer%20just%20issuing%20hunting%20permits%20to%20spending%20the%20remainder%20of%20his%20life%20protecting%20the%20tiger%20and%20its%20habitat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3