%3EStarting%20off%20as%20a%20volunteer%20at%20Madras%20Snake%20Park%20in%201975%20as%20a%20college%20student%2C%20Vijaya%20(known%20to%20her%20friends%20as%20%E2%80%98Viji%E2%80%99)%20would%20go%20on%20to%20not%20only%20become%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20researchers%20of%20turtles%20but%20also%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20its%20conservation.%20To%20understand%20the%20scope%20of%20turtle%20trade%20and%20the%20exploitation%20it%20entailed%2C%20she%20would%20travel%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20this%20country%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98badlands%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20Chambal%20(ravines)%20to%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20tribute%20penned%20by%20freelance%20journalist%20Janaki%20Lenin%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fecologise.in%2F2017%2F04%2F18%2Ftribute-viji-turtle-girl%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEcologise%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20black%20and%20white%20pictures%20she%20took%20of%20the%20gory%20Ridley%20sea%20turtle%20slaughter%20on%20Digha%20beach%20and%20in%20the%20meat%20markets%20of%20Calcutta%2C%20shook%20the%20public%20when%20India%20Today%20magazine%20ran%20them%20in%20the%20early%201980s.%20This%20was%20the%20first%20media%20expose%20ever%20done%20on%20the%20free-for-all%20trade%20in%20sea%20turtles%20and%20highlights%20the%20difference%20one%20individual%20can%20make%20for%20conservation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%20of%20her%20expose%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20immediately%20took%20action%20against%20the%20exploitation%20of%20sea%20turtles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Anne%20Wright%3A%20India%E2%80%99s%20adopted%20daughter%20and%20pioneer%20of%20wildlife%20conservation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%204%20October%2C%202023%2C%20India%20mourned%20the%20loss%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F333222%2Fanne-wright-conservationist-wildlife-protection-act-reserves-project-tiger-legacy-raza-kazmi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnne%20Wright%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pioneering%20conservationist%20who%20dedicated%20over%20five%20decades%20to%20protecting%20India%E2%80%99s%20wildlife.%20This%20daughter%20of%20a%20British%20civil%20servant%20decided%20to%20adopt%20India%20as%20%E2%80%98her%20country%E2%80%99%20and%20worked%20tirelessly%20to%20protect%20its%20fauna.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnne%20was%20a%20true%20changemaker%2C%20breaking%20gender%20barriers%20in%20wildlife%20conservation%2C%20playing%20a%20key%20role%20in%20drafting%20the%20Wildlife%20(Protection)%20Act%20of%201972%2C%20and%20driving%20the%20creation%20of%20numerous%20Protected%20Areas%2C%20including%20Palamau%20Tiger%20Reserve%20and%20Dalma%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary.%20She%20worked%20closely%20with%20local%20communities%20and%20bureaucracies%20to%20make%20lasting%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Late%20Anne%20Wright%20receiving%20an%20award%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FAnne-Wright-Award-1698675452-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-333245%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22